physical_appearance: The image depicts a the constituents of a developing tank. All the components are black in colour, except for a red rim on the developing tank container. The lid of the container is separated from its body, and so is its centre column. There are no visible scratches or marks on the exterior of the components of the developing tank.
sgcool_label_text: Such a tank is used to load reels of photographic film just before the development process, which involves various steps such as the stop bath and the washing of film. This developing tank is part of the darkroom photography equipment that was previously used by The Picture Farm, which was set up by renowned photographer Willie Tang.
context_21: 45 Jalan Pemimpin, #09-00 Foo Wah Industrial Building, Thomson, Singapore
context_20: The set of equipment was used by The Picture Farm Pte Ltd
